items.title: Example from README doesn't work
items.body:
Hello all,

I'm trying to use json-logic, but for some reason, I can't run even an example from the documentation - it returns False instead of True, as expected. At the same time, everything works fine, if I check it via http://jsonlogic.com/play.html
Please, see my code below.

```
(.venv) $ pip freeze | grep json-logic
json-logic-qubit==0.9.1
(.venv) $
(.venv) $ cat test.py
from json_logic import jsonLogic

rules = { "and" : [
  {"<" : [ { "var" : "temp" }, 110 ]},
  {"==" : [ { "var" : "pie.filling" }, "apple" ] }
] }

data = { "temp" : 100, "pie" : { "filling" : "apple" } }

print(jsonLogic(rules, data))
# True
(.venv) $
(.venv) $ python test.py
False
(.venv) $
```

Any ideas, what may be the root of this issue and how can this be fixed?

Thanks,
Viktor
